Diagnosis. Adult body length 22–35mm . Body ground color from piceous to black, with connexivum and corium from pale yellow to orange yellow. Antenniferous tubercles subcylindrical, situated slightly posterior of middle of anteocular region of head; first antennal segment reaching level of apex of clypeus. Rostrum slender. Pronotum uniformly black. Anterolateral angles anterolaterally directed, short, subconical. Hemelytra reaching apex of abdomen. Basal portion of clavus black, apical half pale. Corium from pale to orange-yellow, its extreme apex black, and with a dark central spot varying from barely perceptible to very extensive, forming an almost complete transversal band across hemelytron. Connexival segments black on anterior half or third across their entire width, pale or orange-yellow on posterior portion (
Lent & Wygodzinsky 1979
).

